# Documents the **Scala 3 indentation syntax** (vs
# legacy brace syntax) AND the **cats-effect IOApp
# entry-point pattern** (vs main fn returning Unit).
# Distinct from typical Java `public static void
# main(String[] args)` and from typical Scala 2 `def
# main(args: Array[String]): Unit`.  cats-effect's
# IOApp lets the main fn return `IO[ExitCode]` which
# the runtime evaluates and exits with the proper
# code.  Corpus's **first documented IOApp pattern**
